But in the end, Hannibal lost; Carthage was defeated, and a generation later, the entire city was wrecked. The Battle of Zama, where the Carthaginians and Hannibal were finally defeated, created Rome as the most powerful city in the Mediterranean. How Rome established its world and its empire still [impacts] much of the world.
